{"acceptance_criteria":"","actor":"","agent_state":"","assignee":"mayor/","await_id":"","await_type":"","close_reason":"","closed_at":null,"closed_by_session":"","compacted_at":null,"compacted_at_commit":null,"compaction_level":0,"content_hash":"fa2601bdd0da9bd5f50f205014871b005751c9ffe6388dad562f00fd12eaf45b","created_at":"2026-03-15T04:56:15Z","created_by":"mayor/","crystallizes":0,"defer_until":null,"description":"## Context\n\nWorking on OfficeWorld V3 — complete redesign from dashboard to full product.\n\n## What Was Done\n\n### Phase 1-2 (MERGED but user unhappy — likely needs restart)\n- PR #33: V3 isometric asset pack (19 sprites from Pipeline) — MERGED\n- PR #34: Design system CSS tokens — MERGED\n- PR #35: Agent chat view with message filtering — MERGED\n- PR #36: Isometric campus view with building states — MERGED (I resolved conflicts)\n- PR #37: Linear-style kanban task board — MERGED (I resolved conflicts)\n\n### User Feedback: \"I don't like the work at all\"\nUser rejected ALL of Phase 1-2 output. Problems:\n1. Buildings are colored rectangles (Phaser Graphics), not actual sprites — Pipeline's assets aren't used\n2. Wrong architecture — Phaser canvas with React panels bolted on, feels like two apps\n3. Nothing connects to real data\n4. Phaser is used as primary app shell when it should be the game layer only\n\n### New Vision Discussed (NOT yet implemented)\nThe user wants OfficeWorld to BE Gas Town's interface, not a dashboard on top of it:\n- \"How can we make my setup look like child's play?\"\n- Every GT concept maps to something physical in the office\n- Rooms = Projects, Characters = Agents, Task Board = Beads, Rulebook = SOPs\n- Mailroom = TG/communications, Blueprint Store = templates marketplace\n- 60-second onboarding: pick template → rooms build → agents spawn → work starts\n- User NEVER touches CLI — the game IS the management interface\n- Stardew Valley pixel art style, top-down, mayor character walks around\n- Progressive disclosure through exploration\n\n### Beads Filed (Epic: of-gdt)\n- CLOSED: of-jbt, of-1nw, of-7is, of-8ze (Phase 1-2, merged but quality rejected)\n- OPEN: of-nbe (profiles), of-moa (blueprints), of-x23 (team builder), of-kwb (SOP editor), of-4yp (decoration shop), of-2sk (leaderboard), of-3en (TG integration), of-k4s (onboarding), of-aup (business stack)\n\n### Key Files\n- UX Spec: officeworld/mayor/rig/docs/v3-ux-spec.md\n- Pipeline's spec: image_studio/crew/pipeline/office_world_v3_ux_spec.md\n- Assets: officeworld/mayor/rig/public/assets/v3/ (buildings, campus, furniture sprites)\n- Current code on dev branch at Gitea: http://localhost:3300/Deepwork-AI/OfficeWorld\n\n### Next Steps\n- Need to decide: reset dev and start fresh, or build on top of what's there\n- Restructure beads to match the new \"game IS the product\" vision\n- The game crew member (officeworld/game) was started but may need different instructions\n- All Phase 3 polecats were killed — no work in progress\n- User needs to confirm direction before more polecats are dispatched\n\n### Game Design Discussion\nPresented 3 philosophies: Living Office (Stardew), War Base (CoC), Factory (Factorio).\nUser leaned toward making it \"child's play\" — the office metaphor doing all the teaching.\nNo final decision on game engine yet but Phaser IS right for the game part, React for data panels.","design":"","due_at":null,"ephemeral":0,"estimated_minutes":null,"event_kind":"","external_ref":null,"hook_bead":"","id":"deacon-jtr","is_template":0,"issue_type":"task","last_activity":null,"metadata":"{}","mol_type":"","notes":"","original_size":null,"owner":"prathamonchain@gmail.com","payload":"","pinned":0,"priority":1,"quality_score":null,"rig":"","role_bead":"","role_type":"","sender":"","source_repo":"","source_system":"","spec_id":"","status":"hooked","target":"","timeout_ns":0,"title":"🤝 HANDOFF: OfficeWorld V3 Redesign In Progress","updated_at":"2026-03-15T04:56:16Z","waiters":"","wisp_type":"","work_type":""}
